  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is designed to assess the need to stop Aspirin before laparoscopic inguinal hernia
      repair. It will consist of 2 groups: patients who continue to take Aspirin and patients who
      stop Aspirin 1 week before the surgery. Randomization will be by closed envelope method. The
      surgeon will be blinded for the usage of Aspirin. Primary outcome is the rate of
      post-operative seroma or hematoma within the fist 24 hours after surgery. Secondary outcomes
      are post-operative pain at regular intervals, post-operative seroma and hematoma after 24
      hours and other post-operative complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
